41:41.080 --> 41:44.200
We'll combine the two elements,

41:44.280 --> 41:47.520
and make a show
that no one has ever seen.

41:47.600 --> 41:51.200
It's creative. It's playful.

41:51.280 --> 41:54.160
And with lots of opportunity for profit.

41:55.800 --> 41:57.920
What's this?

41:58.000 --> 41:59.960
I don't get anything!

42:01.640 --> 42:03.920
Uh...

42:04.000 --> 42:08.080
Well, it's usually my boss who...

42:08.160 --> 42:12.720
What these guys want,
I think, is to arrange

42:12.800 --> 42:15.080
- a reindeer race. Right?
- Exactly.

42:15.160 --> 42:16.960
- [Lars] Yes.
- [man] Race.

42:17.040 --> 42:18.720
Why didn't you just say that right away?

42:21.160 --> 42:25.280
[in English] Forget about it. All right?
No way. I am not going back.

42:25.360 --> 42:28.800
It is suicide.
Frank, I talked to Uncle Sal.

42:28.880 --> 42:30.240
He gave me the green light.

42:30.320 --> 42:31.920
You are not listening, my friend.

42:32.000 --> 42:36.000
Okay? No fucking way am I going back.

42:36.080 --> 42:39.920
Christ, Frank, you know Aldo's gonna come
at us with all he's got.

42:40.000 --> 42:42.240
Yeah? Let him come.

42:42.320 --> 42:45.120
All right? I've dealt with him once,
I'll deal with him again.

42:45.200 --> 42:47.840
Where does that leave me?

42:47.920 --> 42:51.720
I covered for you, goddamn it.

42:51.800 --> 42:55.120
Come on, Frankie.
Please, what do you think?

42:55.200 --> 42:58.560
I appreciate what you did,
my friend. I really do.

42:58.640 --> 43:01.960
But this time, I cannot help you.

43:15.160 --> 43:19.000
[Procul Harum's
"The Devil Came from Kansas" playing]
